The paper deals with submodular maximization, which is a problem in discrete optimization and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the concept of adaptivity, which is a fundamental concept in computer science and is studied in various areas such as information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also presents a novel approach that achieves an exponential speedup in parallel running time, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG).
